Cost/price type applied to record¬"Cost_Type"¬"The cost type
column5: varchar(20)"¬"Yes - NCDR"¬"This varies according to data type: A&E - Set as Tariff where the accident and emergency department type is 01
column6: 02 or 03. Where this is not the case
column7: set to local (please note that local payment rules have yet to be defined). APC - Cost_Type is assigned by the following steps in order. Later steps are only used if the field remains null for a record. 1) If Administrative_Category is 02 (private patient) then the record is excluded. 2) If the first four characters of HRG_Code is one of NZ04
column12: NZ09 or NZ10 then MPPS (maternity pathway payment system) is used. 3) If Calc_Type is Tariff
column13: Der_Management_Type is RDA (regular day attender) or RNA (regular night attender) and HRG_Code is anything apart fromSB97ZorSC97Zthen Cost_Type is null. 4) If Calc_Type is Tariff and the first four characters of HRG_Code are one of NZ11
column16: NZ14 or NZ15 Tariff (MPPS) is assigned
column17: in all other cases where Calc_Type is tariff
column18: tariff is used. 5) If no Cost_Type has been added using the previous steps
column19: local is used. OP - Cost_Type is assigned by the following steps in order. Later steps are only used if the field remains null for a record. 1 If attendance Status is anything but 5 (attended on time or
column21: before the relevant care professional was ready to see the patient) or 6 (arrived late
column22: after the relevant care professional was ready to see the patient
column23: but was seen) or Administrative_Category is 02 (private patient) then excluded is assigned. 2) If Treatment_Function_Code is 501 (obstetrics) or 560 (midwifery services) MPPS (maternity pathway payment system) is assigned. 3) If Tariff_Exclusion_Reason is null

column12: and if it is found then the NPoC_Cat for this Service_Line is displayed (only one NPoC_Cat is shown

column5: RDA then RDAY for regular day attender
column6: RNA then RNIGHT for regular night attender
column7: NE then NELNE which is non-elective
column9: where Der_Management_Type is EM then NEL for non-elective (if Spell_PbR_Adj_LoS is less than 2
column10: add ST to make it NELST for short stay non-elective). If none of these rules are met
column11: use APCUNK for Unknown. OP - Where Der_Appointment_Type is New (i.e. not a follow up) which has received a procedure tariff and has a completed Treatment_Function_Code of anything other than 329 then OPPROCFA is used
column12: in the same circumstances but Der_Appointment_Type is Fop it is OPPROCFUP
column13: and if Der_Appointment_Type is not New or FUp then it is OPPROC. If Der_Contact_Type is NF2F and Der_Appointment_Type is New then NF2FFA is used
column14: when Der_Appointment_Type is FUp then NF2FFUP and when Der_Appointment_Type is neither of these
column18: FUp)are looked at. When the record is Cons
column19: Single and New then OPFASPCL is used
column33: Multi and FUp then OPFUPMPNCL is used. If none of these combinations apply
column34: OPFA is applied when Der_Appoinment_Type is New
column35: and OPFUP if it is FUp. Finally
column36: any remaining records are classed as OPAUNK."¬"N/A"¬"N/A"¬"NHSE_SUSPlus_Reporting.THF.APCS

column15: 1 is applied. For all other records that met the initial rules

column1: Service line¬"NCBLocal_FCE_ServiceLine"¬"The local service line for the episode."¬"nvarchar(30)
column3: varchar(8)"¬"Yes - NCDR"¬"Runs through a hierarchy of rules; if one rule has already been met
column4: all proceeding rules are not applied. When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete and the first three characters of Commissioner_Code are a Commissioning Hub code
column5: Local Area Team code (that is not Q99)
column6: X24 or XMB then NCBLocal_FCE_ServiceLine is taken from the derived load table where possible. If this is not complete
column7: Service Lines are looked for in Agreement_Line_Number
column9: and used instead (order of priority as written). When NCBLocal_RuleApplied contains |Provider Submitted and NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is compete
column10: then Service Lines are looked for in Agreement_Line_Number
column11: Commissioner_Reference_Number and Provider_Reference_Number (ignoring the NCB digits at the beginning)
column14: this Service_Line is used (order of priority as written). When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete and FCE_HRG is SB97Z then NCBPS01C is applied. When FCE_HRG is SC97Z then NCBPS01R is applied. When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete and Treatment_Function_Code is 140
column19: 217 or 450 then NCB_Dent is applied. When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete and Agreement_Line_Number
column20: Commissioner_Reference_Number or Provider_Reference_Number contains DENTAL and NCBLocal_RuleApplied does not contain |Secondary Dental NCB_Dent is applied. When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete and GP_Practice_Type_NCB is Military then NCB_Milit is applied. When Der_Record_Type is Curr
column21: NCBLocal_RuleApplied does not contain Military Personnel
column22: GP_Practice_Type_NCB is Military and the first three characters of Commissioner_Code are 13Q then NCB_Milit is applied. When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete
column23: NCBLocal_RuleApplied does not contain Military Personnel
column24: GP_Practice_Type_NCB is not Non-NCB and the first three characters of Commissioner_Code are XMB then NCB_Milit is applied. When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete and GP_Practice_Type_NCB is Offender then NCB_Offd is applied. When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete and Postcode_Type is Unique in the ODS prisons postcode reference table then NCB_Offd is applied. When NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is complete
column25: Postcode_Type is Non Unique or Unknown in the ODS prisons postcode reference table and Source_of_Admission is 39 then NCB_Offd is applied. If none of the previous rules are met
column26: NCBLocal_FCE_Flag is 1 and NCBLocal_RuleApplied contains |Provider Submitted then NCB_Unk is applied."¬"N/A"¬"N/A"¬"NHSE_SUSPlus_Live.dbo.tbl_Data_SEM_APCE_1314_Der

column1: Service line¬"NCBLocal_Spell_ServiceLine"¬"The local service line for the spell
column2: including values submitted by the provider for provider supplied flagged activity."¬"nvarchar(30)
column4: varchar(8)"¬"Yes - NCDR"¬"Set as NCBLocal_Spell_ServiceLine (from the derived table for the relevant year) when it is not null
column5: where it is look in Agreement_Line_Number
column6: Commissioner_Reference_Number and Provider_Reference_Number for a Service Line and use this
column7: applied where the row is not flagged as a duplicate and the first three digits of Commissioner_Code are a Commissioning Hub code
column8: a Local Area Team code (apart from Q99)
column11: Code_Type is Specialised and Service_Line is anything but NCB_Unk. Looks at Agreement_Line_Number
column12: Commissioner_Reference_Number and Provider_Reference_Number to determine if they are equal to a Service_Line with the NCB characters at the start removed
column14: apply the Service_Line it matches to where
column16: Code_Type is Specialised and Service_Line is anything but NCB_Unk and NCBLocal_RuleApplied. Set as NCBPS01C when Spell_Core_HRG is SB97Z and NCBPS01R when Spell_Core_HRG is SC97Z. Set as NCB_Dent when Spell_Treatment_Function_Code (or Der_Dischg_Treatment_Function_Code if null) is one of 140
column21: 217 or 450. Set as NCB_Dent when Agreement_Line_number
column22: Commissioner_Reference_Number or Provider_Reference_Number contain DENTAL and NCBLocal_RuleApplied does not contain Secondary Dental. Set as NCB_Milit when Der_Record_Type is Hist and GP_Practice_Type_NCB is Military. Set as NCB_Milit when Der_Record_Type is Curr
column23: NCBLocal_RuleApplied is complete and does not contain Military Personnel
column24: GP_Practice_Type_NCB is Military and the first three characters of Commissioner_Code are 13Q. Set as NCB_Milit when Der_Record_Type is Hist
column25: GP_Practice_Code is not one of V81997
column27: NCBLocal_RuleApplied is complete and does not contain Military Personnel
column28: GP_Practice_Type is not Non-NCB and the first three characters of Commissioner_Code are XMB. Set as NCB_Offd when GP_Practice_Type_NCB is Offender. Set as NCB_Offd when the patients postcodes Postcode_Type is Unique in the ODS Prisons Postcode reference table and APCS_Last_Ep_Ind is 1. Set as NCB_Offd when APCS_Last_Ep_Ind is 1
column29: Postcode_Type is Non Unique or Unknown and Source_of_Admission is 39. If NCBLocal_Spell_ServiceLine remains null to this point and NCBLocal_RuleApplied contains |Provider Submitted then set to NCB_Unk."¬"N/A"¬"N/A"¬"NHSE_SUSPlus_Reporting.Data.OIC_Intermediate_Table_APC

Tariff exclusion reason¬"Tariff_Exclusion_Reason"¬"Indicates the reason as to why the attendance/spell has been excluded from been priced at national tariff
column6: according to data type: APC - 1) When Administrative_Category is 02 or 2 then Administrative_Category is applied. 2) When Der_Management_Type is RDA or RNA and the first four characters of HRG_Code are anything but SB97
column13: NZ09 or NZ10 then Regular_Day_Or_Night_Attender is applied. 3) When Calc_Type is anything but Tariff then CORE_HRG_EXCLUSION is applied. 4) When HRG_Code is N/A and Spell_PreGrp_Exc_Reason contains overlapping episodes then Overlapping_Epi_In_Spell is applied. 5) When HRG_Code is N/A and Spell_PreGrp_Exc_Reason contains Missing Episode\s then Missing_Episode(S) is applied.5) When HRG_Code is N/A but neither of the above rules are met
column14: Pre_Grouper_Exclusion is applied. 6) In all other cases
column15: left null. OP - 1 When Attendance_Status is anything other than 5 or 6 then Attendance_Status_Exclusion is applied. 2) When Administrative_Category is 02 or 2 then Administrative_Category is applied. 3) When the last character of Commissioning_Serial_Number is = then Commissioning_Serial_Number is applied. 4) When Exc_All_Settings in the HRG Tariff Reference Table is Y then Core_HRG_Exclusion is applied. 5) When the first two characters of Attend_Core_HRG are WF and Main_Specialty_Code is one of 560
column21: 950 or 960 then MAIN_SPECIALTY_CODE is applied. 6) When the first two characters of Attend_Core_HRG are anything but WF
column24: HRG_Code_OPP is incomplete in the cost table and Main_Specialty_Code is one of 900
column29: 950 or 960 then Core_HRG_TFC_Exclusion is applied. 7) When the first two characters of Attend_Core_HRG are WF and Treatment_Function_Code is anything but 501 or 560 then Core_HRG_TFC_Exclusion is applied. 8) When Treatment_Function_Code is 264 or 343 then Core_HRG_TFC_Exclusion is applied. 9) When Attend_Core_HRG is UZ01Z and the first character of Treatment_Function_Code is 7 then Core_HRG_TFC_Exclusion is applied. 10) When the first two characters of Attend_Core_HRG are anything but WF
column32: HRG_Code_OPP in the cost table is incomplete and Treatment_Function_Code is incomplete then Core_HRG_TFC_Exclusion is applied. 11) If none of these rules are met

Tariff type¬"Tariff_Type"¬"The tariff type derived using the AEA_Department_Type field
column7: according to data type: A&E - When AEA_Department_Type is 01 or then 24 hr main is applied
column8: where it is or 02 then mono-spec and where it is of 03 then MIU. APC - Tariff_Type is a concatenation of all tariff types associated with the spell. For each of the rules below
column9: a new code is added to the string
column10: if the rule is met. When Der_Management_Type is DC and Daycase_Tariff (in the HRG reference table) is complete
column11: then day case is applied. When Der_Management_Type is EL and Inpatient_Tariff (in the HRG reference table) is complete
column12: then inpatient is applied. When Der_Management_Type is DC or EL and Elective_Tariff (in the HRG reference table) is complete
column13: then elective is applied. When Der_Management_Type is RDA or RNA and HRG_Code (in the cost table) is SB97Z or SC97Z then Elective is applied. When Der_Management_Type is EM or NE then Non-elective is applied. When Cost_Type starts with Tariff and Spell_BP (in the cost table) is one of BP35
column62: BP52 or ENDO|BPT is added. When Der_Management_Type is EM
column63: Spell_Adj_LoS (in the cost table) is less than 2
column64: Der_Age_at_CDS_Activity_Date is greater than or equal to 19 (or null)
column65: NonElective_ShortStay_Indicator (in the HRG reference table) is 1 and Tariff_Type does not contain |BPT
column66: (or if Tariff_Type does contain |BPT and HRG_Code is DZ16B or DZ16C) then |Short Stay is added. When Cost_Type starts with Tariff and Spell_ExcessBedDays is greater than 0 then |Long Stay is added. When Cost_Type starts with Tariff
column67: Specialised_Top_Up_Indicator (HRG reference table) is 1 and Spell_SSC (cost table) is complete
column68: add |Specialised. When Spell_SSC contains 97 and Tariff_Type does not already contain Specialised then add |Specialised. OP - When Tariff_Exclusion_Reason and Cost_Type are incomplete set as OPP
column69: and add |BPT where BP_Type (in the HRG reference table) is HRG. Set as specialty when Tariff_Exclusion_Reason is null
column74: Der_Staff_Type is Cons and Cost_Type is null."¬"N/A"¬"N/A"¬"NHSE_SUSPlus_Live.dbo.tbl_Data_SEM_AEA_1314_Cost
